00:00:00.300 --> 00:00:04.640
Hello, my name is Colm Clarke, and I've lived in the Carrigans area of County Donegal for most of my life.

00:00:04.780 --> 00:00:08.700
And I've worked in the flax and linen industry up until 1955

00:00:09.020 --> 00:00:16.020
Last year, here at the Monreagh Heritage Centre in County Donegal, we decided to film the process of producing linen.

00:00:16.080 --> 00:00:18.400
There are six steps in the process.

00:00:19.560 --> 00:00:23.080
Step 1: we sow the flax seed in April.

00:00:24.320 --> 00:00:29.200
Step 2: the flax plant grows to full height after three months.

00:00:30.480 --> 00:00:34.800
Step 3: we pull it and put it in a dam to soak for 2 weeks.

00:00:36.520 --> 00:00:39.300
Step 4: Spread it and dry it on a grass field. It takes about ten days.

00:00:39.900 --> 00:00:46.900
Step 5:  Plant is lifted and bundled together into 'stooks' for five days.

00:00:47.340 --> 00:00:51.900
Step 6:  The sixth step of the process is by hand, ready for the mill to produce linen.

00:00:55.360 --> 00:00:57.360
Now we're ready to sow the flax

